div.p:
THE Great Applauſe you have ſo deſervedly meritted, hath
encouraged me to Dedicate this ſmall Epitomy to Your Honour; and not knowing any Man, that can with more lively Colours repreſent this Important Affair to the Wiſdom of the Nation, I lay it at Your Lordſhip's Feet, as an UNDERTAKING, (which if Your Grace be pleaſed to Eſpouſe, for the Good of the Kingdom) you will thereby add another Trophy to your former Atchievements;
and the Glory of the Action will be Recorded to all Poſterity: For upon a National-Fiſhery, under God, doth depend the Safety, Honour, and Happineſs of this Kingdom, the Flouriſhing of Trade, and the Supporting of Credit, as in the Sequel of my Diſcourſe, I hope, I have made appear.
